      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a bit harsh lol, im just trying to do my job right. But i get what u mean about the brands. When u say \"urban\" or \"the real deal\" though, aren't u referring to specific communities? Like, when people talk about that authentic vibe, does it stem from a specific demographic or neighborhood look? i want to make sure the color palettes and the \"attitude\" i'm designing for actually match the people who live that lifestyle.",
